  "text": "The position detection performance of the proposed model is shown in Table 9 . The table shows that the correct position was detected with an F-measure of 90%. Five different approaches were given in [CITATION_1] .The descriptions of these approaches are given in [CITATION_2] . These approaches achieved a very low accuracy range (59-65%) which made the authors in [CITATION_3] to suggest further investigations. In this paper, we partially resolved this issue using the deep learning approach which improved the average position detection by 25%, as shown in Figure 9 . Table 9 . Precision, Recall, and F-measure of the proposed model for subject-independent position detection. F-measure for the subject-independent position detection",
